article.description: Trey Murphy III had a career-high 25 points with five 3-pointers as Rice rallied to beat Northwestern State 80-74 on Tuesday night to win its third straight.
article.headline: Murphy leads Rice past Northwestern St. 80-74
article.linkText: Murphy leads Rice past Northwestern St. 80-74
article.story: NATCHITOCHES, La. -- Trey Murphy III had a career-high 25 points with five 3-pointers as Rice rallied to beat Northwestern State 80-74 on Tuesday night to win its third straight. Drew Peterson had 15 points for Rice (3-1), which trailed 38-30 at halftime. Ako Adams added 14 points and Payton Moore had 10. Brian White had 26 points for the Demons (1-2). Jamaure Gregg added 11 points and Chudier Bile had 10. Rice faces UC Santa Barbara on the road on Saturday. Northwestern State takes on Tulane on the road on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
